  "properties": {
    "title": "Hourly synoptic observations from fixed-land stations (SYNOP) - UK",	
    "description": "Hourly land surface observations (SYNOP) are standardized meteorological reports which form a component of the Global Basic Observing Network (GBON). In the UK, these observations are collected by automated weather stations. Each report should include as a minimum: air temperature, dew point, atmospheric pressure, wind speed and direction, precipitation and snow depth, with some UK stations also reporting cloud cover and types, visibility, weather phenomena, sunshine duration, and state of ground. Reports are in BUFR format.",	
